504
00:34:34,872 --> 00:34:37,170
Maybe have that lake
full of trout and bass...

505
00:34:38,910 --> 00:34:41,606
nice outdoor eatery
on that pier down yonder...

506
00:34:44,315 --> 00:34:46,840
a place where people
could get a cold drink,

507
00:34:46,918 --> 00:34:48,579
admire the beauty again.

508
00:34:50,221 --> 00:34:53,190
Now you're talking.
It sounds pretty good to me.

509
00:34:58,729 --> 00:35:00,458
Well, Merl, I gotta get on to work.

510
00:35:00,531 --> 00:35:02,396
Nice to make your acquaintance.

511
00:35:02,467 --> 00:35:03,991
Pleasure was mine.

512
00:35:04,068 --> 00:35:05,399
Thank you for the coffee.

513
00:35:06,604 --> 00:35:08,196
Keep the wheels turning.

514
00:35:12,577 --> 00:35:14,408
There you go.

515
00:35:18,850 --> 00:35:22,809
If you eat a little more food,
you can be sleeping in your own bed.

516
00:35:22,887 --> 00:35:24,149
Won't that be nice?

517
00:35:26,290 --> 00:35:30,090
Yeah, that's it.

518
00:35:31,095 --> 00:35:32,323
It's good, huh?

519
00:35:33,464 --> 00:35:35,864
Vanilla custard, yes indeed.

520
00:35:37,502 --> 00:35:41,165
Yes, that's my good girl.

521
00:35:43,908 --> 00:35:46,274
I want you out of my house.

522
00:35:47,345 --> 00:35:48,403
What, Ma?

523
00:35:49,480 --> 00:35:52,608
Get that crap away from me,
you kiss-ass.

524
00:35:52,683 --> 00:35:57,711
All you want is that meringue recipe,
and it'll never happen.

525
00:35:57,788 --> 00:36:01,121
You couldn't cook
your way out of a Ziploc.

526
00:36:01,192 --> 00:36:04,161
No wonder you could
never hold on to a man.

527
00:36:05,163 --> 00:36:09,327
You're going to end up a lesbian
if you're not one already.

528
00:36:10,334 --> 00:36:11,858
Evening, miss.

529
00:36:13,804 --> 00:36:14,964
Hello.

530
00:36:16,507 --> 00:36:18,236
I hate your guts.

531
00:36:18,309 --> 00:36:19,936
I don't care.

532
00:36:20,011 --> 00:36:22,844
I have never asked you
for one thing, God damn...

533
00:36:22,914 --> 00:36:24,040
Then don't.

534
00:36:24,115 --> 00:36:27,414
You are gonna cough up
that fucking recipe.

535
00:36:27,485 --> 00:36:29,919
Dream on, you old maid.

536
00:36:29,987 --> 00:36:31,511
Don't push me.

537
00:36:31,689 --> 00:36:33,054
Don't push <i>me.</i>

538
00:37:06,557 --> 00:37:08,718
Ma, I brought your favorite.

539
00:37:10,695 --> 00:37:11,787
Ma?

540
00:37:13,264 --> 00:37:14,390
Penny?

541
00:37:18,936 --> 00:37:24,670
For today we are mourning the loss
of two remarkable individuals...

542
00:37:26,077 --> 00:37:30,343
Penny Varrow,
a willful woman of character

543
00:37:30,414 --> 00:37:32,974
who led an independent life,

544
00:37:33,050 --> 00:37:38,955
most recently running a crisis center
for abandoned spouses...

545
00:37:39,023 --> 00:37:40,786
and Ruth Tuckby,

546
00:37:40,858 --> 00:37:46,091
devoted mother, wife,
and local knitting legend,

547
00:37:46,163 --> 00:37:51,032
who strove to make
the lives of those around her richer.

548
00:37:51,102 --> 00:37:54,560
They were both good women

549
00:37:54,639 --> 00:37:58,871
who celebrated their differences
throughout a rocky relationship.

550
00:38:01,646 --> 00:38:05,446
Well, ultimately celebrated them
a little too much, I reckon.

551
00:38:13,357 --> 00:38:14,790
Mark. Mark!

552
00:38:22,400 --> 00:38:23,594
Mark!

553
00:38:23,668 --> 00:38:24,657
Shut up.

554
00:38:24,735 --> 00:38:25,759
- Mark.
- Ray.

555
00:38:26,804 --> 00:38:28,203
Hey, Clem.

556
00:38:28,272 --> 00:38:30,797
I'm... I'm sorry for your loss.

557
00:38:32,310 --> 00:38:36,508
I know this is not the best time
to talk business, but...

558
00:38:36,580 --> 00:38:37,842
That's okay.

559
00:38:37,915 --> 00:38:40,213
The bulk of the estate goes
to you and your brother.

560
00:38:40,284 --> 00:38:42,081
The house, as you may know,

561
00:38:42,153 --> 00:38:44,451
was pretty heavily leveraged
awhile back,

562
00:38:44,522 --> 00:38:47,923
plus she didn't have much
in the way of medical coverage.

563
00:38:49,060 --> 00:38:50,288
Right.

564
00:38:50,361 --> 00:38:54,195
Son, this here's your share.

565
00:38:56,400 --> 00:38:57,958
Thanks for all your help, Clem.

566
00:38:58,035 --> 00:38:59,059
Sorry.

567
00:39:00,071 --> 00:39:02,062
Oh, I forgot to give you this.

568
00:39:02,139 --> 00:39:03,936
Your mama wanted you to have it.

569
00:39:06,644 --> 00:39:08,703
Well, if there's
anything else you need,

570
00:39:08,779 --> 00:39:11,612
I'll be in Ridgecrest,
bored to tears.

571
00:39:39,910 --> 00:39:42,743
Eddie? You got a minute?

572
00:39:42,813 --> 00:39:44,371
Not today, Ray.
I'm busy.

573
00:39:46,083 --> 00:39:47,948
I need to speak to you, son.

574
00:39:48,018 --> 00:39:49,349
R'ch'lle, excuse us.

575
00:39:50,354 --> 00:39:51,412
Here you go.

576
00:39:55,526 --> 00:39:56,550
What is it?

577
00:39:57,628 --> 00:39:58,890
I got something for you.

578
00:39:59,764 --> 00:40:01,095
Like what?

579
00:40:01,165 --> 00:40:02,359
You should have this.

580
00:40:02,433 --> 00:40:04,993
Your grandma
would've wanted it that way.

581
00:40:05,069 --> 00:40:06,229
Go on, take it.

582
00:40:11,409 --> 00:40:13,274
Eleven hundred bucks?

583
00:40:13,344 --> 00:40:14,641
For college.

584
00:40:14,712 --> 00:40:16,179
College?

585
00:40:18,282 --> 00:40:20,147
What the hell's
the matter with you, Ray?

586
00:40:20,217 --> 00:40:23,050
I got better things to do
with this money and my time

587
00:40:23,120 --> 00:40:24,985
than get some stupid education.

588
00:40:26,724 --> 00:40:28,783
Me and R'ch'lle
is moving in together.

589
00:40:31,729 --> 00:40:33,219
I just wanted to say that...

590
00:40:34,298 --> 00:40:37,699
even though we both know
you're not my own flesh and blood...

591
00:40:39,170 --> 00:40:41,070
I still love you, son.

592
00:40:42,339 --> 00:40:45,172
Hey, let's get a move on.
I'm gonna be late for work.

593
00:40:48,512 --> 00:40:50,639
Dirk offered me a gig.

594
00:40:50,714 --> 00:40:52,579
I'm finally gonna make
some real coin.

595
00:40:52,650 --> 00:40:54,049
That's a dead end, Ed.

596
00:40:54,118 --> 00:40:55,278
Not to me, it ain't.

597
00:40:55,352 --> 00:40:58,219
Ed, this train is leaving the station.

598
00:40:59,557 --> 00:41:00,615
Ed...

599
00:41:02,793 --> 00:41:03,987
I'll see you around.

600
00:41:05,129 --> 00:41:07,154
If you need anything, son,
you let me know.

601
00:41:07,231 --> 00:41:09,358
Yeah. All right.

602
00:41:35,059 --> 00:41:37,391
Dirk's boys held up
the delivery truck again.

603
00:41:37,461 --> 00:41:39,691
All we got left
is Shake 'n Bake, aisle five.

604
00:41:40,698 --> 00:41:42,825
But... we're out of chicken.

605
00:41:44,568 --> 00:41:45,728
These'll do me.

606
00:41:46,937 --> 00:41:48,871
I was going to eat light
tonight anyhow.

607
00:41:53,444 --> 00:41:57,847
Pork rinds and a large bag
of ranch-flavored sunflower seeds.

608
00:41:59,083 --> 00:42:00,482
Anything to drink with that?

609
00:42:00,551 --> 00:42:03,577
Nah. Plenty of water in the tap,
I always say.

610
00:42:06,023 --> 00:42:09,049
I bet you could use
a home-cooked meal one of these days.

611
00:42:09,126 --> 00:42:10,787
Yeah, well...

612
00:42:17,535 --> 00:42:19,298
Sorry about you and Charlene...

613
00:42:20,337 --> 00:42:21,565
and your mom...

614
00:42:23,107 --> 00:42:24,506
and Penny.

615
00:42:25,609 --> 00:42:28,134
Trying to look at it
as a new beginning.

616
00:42:28,212 --> 00:42:29,804
May take me awhile to get there.

617
00:42:31,315 --> 00:42:33,840
Anyway, thanks
for coming to the funeral.

618
00:42:33,918 --> 00:42:35,112
Saw you sitting in back.

619
00:42:35,185 --> 00:42:36,584
Oh, my pleasure, Ray.

620
00:42:38,188 --> 00:42:39,587
So, what are you doing later?

621
00:42:41,091 --> 00:42:43,753
Later, like... tonight later?

622
00:42:43,827 --> 00:42:46,318
Yeah, for a start.

623
00:42:46,397 --> 00:42:48,627
Well, I'll probably just go home

624
00:42:48,699 --> 00:42:52,465
and sort through all
the death papers and stuff, I guess.

625
00:42:53,470 --> 00:42:54,459
You?

626
00:42:54,538 --> 00:42:57,996
I'd really like to go
into Ridgecrest and see a movie.

627
00:42:58,075 --> 00:42:59,804
- It's been awhile.
- Yeah?

628
00:42:59,877 --> 00:43:03,176
Maybe get a bite after at that
new Arby's folks are talking about?

629
00:43:03,247 --> 00:43:05,647
Oh, yeah. I drove by it
a couple times.

630
00:43:05,716 --> 00:43:07,650
Might be worth checking out.

631
00:43:14,391 --> 00:43:16,951
Well... see you soon, Nora.

632
00:43:17,027 --> 00:43:18,551
Hope so, Ray.

633
00:44:55,592 --> 00:44:56,616
Nora.

634
00:44:58,162 --> 00:45:00,153
You wanna go on a date...

635
00:45:00,230 --> 00:45:01,561
with me?

636
00:45:01,632 --> 00:45:04,567
Been waiting 18 years
for you to ask.

637
00:46:50,974 --> 00:46:52,965
Where'd you get
all this fresh food?

638
00:46:53,043 --> 00:46:56,171
Got up bright and early this morning,
drove special out to Ridgecrest.

639
00:46:56,246 --> 00:46:57,304
Cook it yourself?

640
00:46:58,882 --> 00:47:01,942
That's about the sweetest thing
anyone's ever done for me.

641
00:47:02,019 --> 00:47:04,214
I mean, that is,
if you did do it for me.

642
00:47:04,288 --> 00:47:05,380
I did.

643
00:47:07,958 --> 00:47:11,086
Ray, how come you never got
out of here when you had the chance?

644
00:47:11,161 --> 00:47:13,129
Me? I don't know.

645
00:47:14,298 --> 00:47:16,994
I know you got that offer
a few years back, going to L.A.,

646
00:47:17,067 --> 00:47:18,762
work for that friend of your dad's.

647
00:47:20,470 --> 00:47:21,732
Didn't suit me, I guess.

648
00:47:25,075 --> 00:47:26,235
This is my home.

649
00:47:27,711 --> 00:47:28,973
I used to love it here.

650
00:47:30,981 --> 00:47:32,471
Summers felt endless.

651
00:47:33,483 --> 00:47:34,814
Swimming, fishing,

652
00:47:34,885 --> 00:47:37,445
just being able to breath
all that cool, fresh air.

653
00:47:38,522 --> 00:47:41,116
I hold on to those memories,
a lot of other ones, too.

654
00:47:42,559 --> 00:47:44,083
Like that one in second grade

655
00:47:44,161 --> 00:47:47,130
when Mrs. Kinney took us
on that field trip to this very spot

656
00:47:47,197 --> 00:47:49,563
and I got a baked bean
stuck in my nose?

657
00:47:49,633 --> 00:47:51,328
You remember that?

658
00:47:51,401 --> 00:47:53,631
I wouldn't stop crying.

659
00:47:53,704 --> 00:47:56,138
You came right over,
just like a little prince.

660
00:47:56,206 --> 00:47:57,867
You picked me up
and you carried me

661
00:47:57,941 --> 00:47:59,238
all the way back to the bus.

662
00:48:00,377 --> 00:48:03,278
I thought it was so romantic...

663
00:48:03,347 --> 00:48:05,747
except maybe that part
about you insisting

664
00:48:05,816 --> 00:48:07,306
on trying to fish the thing out

665
00:48:07,384 --> 00:48:09,784
with one of your dad's
pipe cleaners.

666
00:48:09,853 --> 00:48:12,048
Doctor said you nearly
gave me a lobotomy.

667
00:48:12,122 --> 00:48:14,352
Yeah, I managed to block
that out, actually.

668
00:48:14,424 --> 00:48:15,618
Oh, you did?

669
00:48:19,162 --> 00:48:20,925
I thought it was sweet.

670
00:48:20,998 --> 00:48:23,660
How concerned you were about me,
how much you cared.

671
00:48:23,734 --> 00:48:25,827
Yeah, well...

672
00:48:28,672 --> 00:48:29,832
What about you?

673
00:48:30,841 --> 00:48:32,536
Didn't you ever think
about leaving?

674
00:48:32,609 --> 00:48:34,839
From time to time.

675
00:48:34,912 --> 00:48:36,675
How come you never did, then?

676
00:48:36,747 --> 00:48:38,681
That cheerleading scholarship to UOP

677
00:48:38,749 --> 00:48:40,649
sure was a big deal
for you to turn down.

678
00:48:41,919 --> 00:48:43,386
A girl has her reasons.

679
00:49:04,174 --> 00:49:05,869
I had a wonderful afternoon, Ray.

680
00:49:05,943 --> 00:49:07,103
Me, too, Nora.

681
00:49:08,478 --> 00:49:10,309
Now, I want you to keep
those leftovers.

682
00:49:10,380 --> 00:49:12,405
I made extra
for you to take to work all week.

683
00:49:12,482 --> 00:49:13,506
You sure?

684
00:49:13,583 --> 00:49:16,017
You can't eat packaged food
the rest of your life.

685
00:49:16,086 --> 00:49:18,179
That stuff'll kill you.

686
00:49:18,255 --> 00:49:21,622
Getting a real home-cooked meal
like that sure was something else.

687
00:49:28,899 --> 00:49:34,166
Listen, I know how you must be
feeling about Eddie and all.

688
00:49:40,043 --> 00:49:42,477
You always had
the most beautiful heart, Ray.

689
00:49:47,417 --> 00:49:50,853
Well, I've got to get back to my shift,
so I'll talk on you?

690
00:49:51,755 --> 00:49:52,915
Okay.

691
00:50:59,556 --> 00:51:01,353
Where's my mom and dad?

692
00:51:13,036 --> 00:51:14,264
Yeah?

693
00:51:14,337 --> 00:51:15,599
Dirk here?

694
00:51:15,672 --> 00:51:18,106
Saw him around awhile ago.

695
00:51:18,175 --> 00:51:19,335
Dirk?

696
00:51:20,343 --> 00:51:21,469
Dirk!

697
00:51:23,280 --> 00:51:26,579
Oh, I forgot.
He's up at the plant up the street,

698
00:51:26,650 --> 00:51:28,743
but you ain't supposed
to go up there.

699
00:51:33,490 --> 00:51:35,481
Adjust that... adjust that choke.

700
00:51:35,559 --> 00:51:37,390
Hand me that wrench.

701
00:51:43,867 --> 00:51:47,394
Boy, all these leaky drums sure look
like an accident waiting to happen.

702
00:51:47,471 --> 00:51:49,598
What are you doing here?
You ain't allowed.

703
00:51:49,673 --> 00:51:52,164
Well, I wanna talk
to you about my son.

704
00:51:53,176 --> 00:51:55,667
I'd like it if you didn't drag him
into your line of work.

705
00:51:55,745 --> 00:51:57,269
He ain't even yours, old man.

706
00:51:57,347 --> 00:51:59,747
I'm just saying you
don't need him working for you,

707
00:51:59,816 --> 00:52:01,113
all the guys you got.

708
00:52:03,186 --> 00:52:04,813
Do me this favor, Dirk.

709
00:52:06,756 --> 00:52:08,917
- Favor?
- Yeah, this one time.

710
00:52:08,992 --> 00:52:10,687
I ought to kick your ass right now.

711
00:52:10,760 --> 00:52:12,159
I don't want trouble, Dirk.

712
00:52:12,229 --> 00:52:14,754
I'm just saying it'd be
a nice thing for you to do,

713
00:52:14,831 --> 00:52:17,356
letting him have
a proper shot at a future.

714
00:52:17,434 --> 00:52:18,799
He's a real good kid.

715
00:52:18,869 --> 00:52:21,235
I know. That's why
he's gonna be working for me.

716
00:52:21,304 --> 00:52:23,067
No, but see...

717
00:52:24,941 --> 00:52:28,342
Only thing I see is
a pathetic jerk who's trespassing.

718
00:52:28,411 --> 00:52:30,936
You tell your neighbors
to pay their rent.

719
00:52:32,182 --> 00:52:34,013
Get the fuck off my property.

720
00:52:34,084 --> 00:52:35,415
Bitch.

721
00:52:57,274 --> 00:52:59,139
You pay the rent yet, Den?

722
00:52:59,209 --> 00:53:01,143
Oh, not real... really.

723
00:53:01,211 --> 00:53:02,473
We've been through this.

724
00:53:02,546 --> 00:53:04,878
You're letting everybody down
when you don't.

725
00:53:06,216 --> 00:53:07,444
Ray, I know that.

726
00:53:07,517 --> 00:53:10,577
Denny, you better do something
about the heat, goddamn it.

727
00:53:10,654 --> 00:53:12,281
I'm bustin' a gasket in here.

728
00:53:14,658 --> 00:53:16,489
<i>I don't want him getting into drugs.</i>

729
00:53:18,428 --> 00:53:19,793
I don't care if I'm not...

730
00:53:21,431 --> 00:53:24,730
Then you tell his real father
to take responsibility for once

731
00:53:24,801 --> 00:53:26,530
and give the boy some guidance.

732
00:53:27,537 --> 00:53:28,663
Charlene?

733
00:53:54,698 --> 00:53:57,258
Here's your rent.
It's too hot to stand on ceremony.

734
00:53:57,334 --> 00:53:58,767
So you walk that over to Dirk's

735
00:53:58,835 --> 00:54:01,303
and you tell him to turn
the power back on, okay?

736
00:54:01,371 --> 00:54:03,032
Roger that, Ray.

737
00:54:03,106 --> 00:54:04,539
I'll make good.
I swear.

738
00:54:04,608 --> 00:54:07,099
Soon, Den.
I can't swing two rents.

739
00:54:07,177 --> 00:54:09,941
Get Selma to quit smoking the ice
and pay your bills.

740
00:54:10,013 --> 00:54:11,071
We clear?

741
00:54:11,147 --> 00:54:12,671
Oh, we're clear as day.

742
00:54:15,218 --> 00:54:18,119
Well, I'm gonna have to
put a shirt on.

743
00:54:18,188 --> 00:54:19,416
Then I'll get on it.

744
00:54:23,093 --> 00:54:25,186
Twirling action, like this here.

745
00:54:25,262 --> 00:54:26,923
That's right.
You like that?

746
00:54:26,997 --> 00:54:29,431
See? Yeah? Help yourself.
Take everything.

747
00:54:29,499 --> 00:54:31,399
Next time bring your cars.

748
00:54:31,468 --> 00:54:32,560
You got 'em all?

749
00:54:32,636 --> 00:54:35,196
I got as many Huggies
as I can carry.

750
00:54:35,272 --> 00:54:37,467
I'm gonna sell this shit on eBay.

751
00:54:37,540 --> 00:54:40,100
The free washer fluid
sure was a nice touch.

752
00:54:40,176 --> 00:54:42,974
Look, Nora, you just
swipe your credit card and go.

753
00:54:43,046 --> 00:54:45,139
Kind of feels
like we're in the big city.

754
00:54:46,383 --> 00:54:47,714
Hey, you guys.

755
00:54:47,784 --> 00:54:49,581
- Hey, Stryker.
- Hi, Nora.

756
00:54:49,653 --> 00:54:51,450
This place is just gorgeous.

757
00:54:51,521 --> 00:54:54,115
Thank you.
I'm very, very proud of it.

758
00:54:54,190 --> 00:54:57,956
All I ask is every once in a while
you come on in and fill up a tank.

759
00:54:58,028 --> 00:54:59,757
- Sure.
- Yeah, okay.

