Where you trying to get to?

1011
01:13:25,033 --> 01:13:26,398
Bakersfield.

1012
01:13:28,003 --> 01:13:31,666
Highway is just down yonder.

1013
01:13:31,740 --> 01:13:33,765
How can I ever repay you?

1014
01:13:55,831 --> 01:13:57,355
Hey, what are you doing here?

1015
01:14:02,805 --> 01:14:04,170
Coming!

1016
01:14:05,174 --> 01:14:06,163
Yeah?

1017
01:14:08,644 --> 01:14:10,942
Hey there! Excuse me.

1018
01:14:12,948 --> 01:14:15,280
What the hell you doing?
Get out of my house!

1019
01:14:26,662 --> 01:14:28,596
Never did appreciate that breed.

1020
01:14:44,413 --> 01:14:46,881
That's quite a talent
your wife's got there.

1021
01:14:48,417 --> 01:14:50,282
She do parties as well?

1022
01:14:51,520 --> 01:14:53,283
Knock it off, you perv.

1023
01:14:53,355 --> 01:14:55,380
- Is he dead?
- Candy, get out here!

1024
01:14:55,457 --> 01:14:56,719
There's a dead guy.

1025
01:14:56,792 --> 01:14:58,692
Shut up!
You'll wake the baby.

1026
01:14:58,760 --> 01:15:00,625
Boy, am I glad Denny shoots blanks.

1027
01:15:02,030 --> 01:15:03,019
Okay, let's go.

1028
01:15:03,098 --> 01:15:05,498
I'll hand him up to you.
You start loading the truck.

1029
01:15:05,567 --> 01:15:08,434
Just so you know,
babies give me the heebie-jeebies.

1030
01:15:11,740 --> 01:15:13,935
Good job, Den.
Come on.

1031
01:15:17,279 --> 01:15:18,439
Come on.

1032
01:15:30,626 --> 01:15:32,491
Remember, Selma, be gentle.

1033
01:15:33,529 --> 01:15:34,655
Go on.

1034
01:15:37,633 --> 01:15:39,066
Yuck.

1035
01:15:42,638 --> 01:15:44,230
So what's it gonna be, tough guy?

1036
01:15:44,306 --> 01:15:46,103
Join the resistance
or get vaporized?

1037
01:15:52,281 --> 01:15:54,579
That's our cue.
Come on.

1038
01:15:54,650 --> 01:15:56,083
Just another minute.

1039
01:15:56,151 --> 01:15:57,482
Well, here goes.

1040
01:15:57,553 --> 01:16:00,113
Gonna make ourselves
a whole new future, gentlemen.

1041
01:16:01,990 --> 01:16:03,048
What's wrong?

1042
01:16:03,125 --> 01:16:06,617
I was just kinda hoping
I could push the button, Mr. Tuckby.

1043
01:16:07,629 --> 01:16:09,597
I really like blowin' shit up.

1044
01:16:09,665 --> 01:16:12,634
All right, but
no funny business, you hear?

1045
01:16:12,701 --> 01:16:14,032
Tits!

1046
01:16:18,273 --> 01:16:20,138
Get the truck
and take him to the dump.

1047
01:16:21,009 --> 01:16:22,203
For real, Dirk?

1048
01:16:22,277 --> 01:16:23,972
Deal with it, goddamn it!

1049
01:16:24,046 --> 01:16:26,913
This is for calling me an idiot
every day of my life, Dirk.

1050
01:16:34,790 --> 01:16:36,815
Go get a potato sack and some twine.

1051
01:16:36,892 --> 01:16:38,450
I'll go get the truck.

1052
01:16:42,998 --> 01:16:44,192
What the... hey!

1053
01:16:46,501 --> 01:16:49,527
That's for giving me
heat rash, mo-fo.

1054
01:16:49,605 --> 01:16:50,799
<i>It can go boy, it can go girl.</i>

1055
01:16:50,872 --> 01:16:53,136
Scotty, you do whatever
the hell you want with him.

1056
01:16:53,208 --> 01:16:55,733
<i>It's not just for a girly girl</i>
<i>or a boy.</i>

1057
01:16:56,778 --> 01:16:57,745
Do it again.

1058
01:17:11,493 --> 01:17:13,188
Oh, my Lord.

1059
01:17:13,261 --> 01:17:15,229
I think I fudged my pants.

1060
01:17:22,504 --> 01:17:23,766
Oh, those babies.

1061
01:17:23,839 --> 01:17:26,273
I just want to eat them up,
they're so precious.

1062
01:17:33,081 --> 01:17:34,605
There it is.

1063
01:17:38,353 --> 01:17:40,082
Shit, man, that was fun.

1064
01:17:43,025 --> 01:17:44,617
My God, we've done good, Ray.

1065
01:17:46,061 --> 01:17:49,292
Just like that game we won
against Solvang back in '89

1066
01:17:49,364 --> 01:17:53,323
when I made that key block
and basically walked into the end zone.

1067
01:17:54,870 --> 01:17:56,804
You remember, right, Ray?

1068
01:17:56,872 --> 01:17:58,032
My key block?

1069
01:17:59,141 --> 01:18:02,975
<i>Turned out the little twerp</i>
<i>wasn't that hard to take down.</i>

1070
01:18:03,045 --> 01:18:06,173
<i>Just a bit of guts</i>
<i>and determination from all of us,</i>

1071
01:18:06,248 --> 01:18:11,276
<i>Dirk and company went over faster</i>
<i>than a one-legged cat in a sand box.</i>

1072
01:18:16,258 --> 01:18:17,850
Let us down!

1073
01:18:25,000 --> 01:18:26,126
Good job, guys.

1074
01:18:26,201 --> 01:18:27,668
Pleasure's right here, Ray.

1075
01:18:29,971 --> 01:18:32,439
Get this thing off of me.
Somebody help!

1076
01:18:33,542 --> 01:18:35,476
That hurts, goddamn it.

1077
01:18:37,813 --> 01:18:39,542
Let's get the record straight, punk.

1078
01:18:39,614 --> 01:18:41,275
You're going to apologize right now

1079
01:18:41,349 --> 01:18:44,477
for making life a dark, ugly experience
in this here community,

1080
01:18:44,553 --> 01:18:46,612
or Scotty's going to teach you
what true pain is.

1081
01:18:46,688 --> 01:18:48,155
We clear?

1082
01:18:48,223 --> 01:18:49,281
Eat me.

1083
01:18:50,592 --> 01:18:52,287
Got another surprise for you.

1084
01:18:52,360 --> 01:18:53,190
Merl?

1085
01:18:55,530 --> 01:18:58,260
Sasquatch Two,
this is Sasquatch One.

1086
01:18:58,333 --> 01:19:00,460
We're ready
for Operation Clean Sweep.

1087
01:19:00,535 --> 01:19:01,900
<i>Roger that, Sasquatch One.</i>

1088
01:19:01,970 --> 01:19:05,462
You and your cohorts
are going to take a nice long time out.

1089
01:19:05,540 --> 01:19:06,529
Gentlemen.

1090
01:19:06,608 --> 01:19:08,633
No fucking way.
I didn't do nothing.

1091
01:19:08,710 --> 01:19:10,371
Well, we don't see it that way.

1092
01:19:13,048 --> 01:19:14,743
Take care now.

1093
01:19:14,816 --> 01:19:15,840
Somebody help me.

1094
01:19:17,519 --> 01:19:20,886
Candy, Tammy, Wanda, Jeanine?

1095
01:19:20,956 --> 01:19:24,790
I made this town.
I made this town what it is.

1096
01:19:24,860 --> 01:19:26,919
You all have roofs over your head
because of me,

1097
01:19:26,995 --> 01:19:28,792
all of your ugly-ass heads.

1098
01:19:28,864 --> 01:19:31,458
Oh, no.
He's gonna be crying.

1099
01:19:31,533 --> 01:19:34,468
He's going to prison,
gonna learn his lesson.

1100
01:19:34,536 --> 01:19:37,471
He's off.
Oh, hey.

1101
01:19:37,539 --> 01:19:39,302
Hey, hold on, hold on.

1102
01:19:39,374 --> 01:19:41,501
Can I just say a few more things?

1103
01:19:42,744 --> 01:19:45,235
What if I, like, turn over
a whole new loaf,

1104
01:19:45,313 --> 01:19:47,144
or whatever that is,
and I'll change?

1105
01:19:47,215 --> 01:19:48,239
Sorry, Spoon.

1106
01:19:48,316 --> 01:19:51,217
You go clean up and come back,
and we'll make nice, deal?

1107
01:19:51,286 --> 01:19:53,811
All right, deal.
Wait, you're pinching my wrist.

1108
01:20:13,074 --> 01:20:16,168
Ray, you know, my wife is
in need of a little rehab herself.

1109
01:20:16,244 --> 01:20:18,610
I was thinking maybe
we could put her on a bus.

1110
01:20:18,680 --> 01:20:20,875
You're gonna have
to deal with that on your own.

1111
01:20:22,784 --> 01:20:25,048
God, I hate to piss that woman off.

1112
01:20:30,025 --> 01:20:31,583
Right on schedule.

1113
01:20:34,095 --> 01:20:36,063
Those girls over there.

1114
01:20:36,131 --> 01:20:37,462
Well, Ray...

1115
01:20:37,532 --> 01:20:39,022
I'll see you around.

1116
01:20:55,617 --> 01:20:57,448
Well, what now, Ray?

1117
01:20:58,887 --> 01:21:00,684
I guess that's up to us.

1118
01:21:07,195 --> 01:21:08,822
<i>You know how they say</i>

1119
01:21:08,897 --> 01:21:12,628
<i>"The more things change,</i>
<i>the more they stay the same"?</i>

1120
01:21:16,137 --> 01:21:17,365
<i>Well...</i>

1121
01:21:43,832 --> 01:21:46,096
Can you believe this?

1122
01:22:03,018 --> 01:22:04,952
Sounds nice.

1123
01:22:09,691 --> 01:22:10,851
Nora...

1124
01:22:13,895 --> 01:22:16,523
Remember awhile back,
you asked me why I never left Trona?

1125
01:22:16,598 --> 01:22:19,066
Yes, I do.

1126
01:22:19,134 --> 01:22:23,036
Well, it was 'cause of you.

1127
01:22:24,172 --> 01:22:26,732
This place is hell, Nora,

1128
01:22:26,808 --> 01:22:29,709
but knowing I'd get to come through
that Rite-Valu door every day

1129
01:22:29,778 --> 01:22:32,178
and see your sweet face
made it paradise.

1130
01:22:33,448 --> 01:22:34,642
Ditto.

1131
01:22:44,826 --> 01:22:46,350
What the hey was that?

1132
01:22:48,229 --> 01:22:49,992
It's called a French kiss.

1133
01:22:50,065 --> 01:22:51,259
A what?

1134
01:22:52,267 --> 01:22:55,259
It's a little more intimate
than a regular kiss.

1135
01:22:55,337 --> 01:22:58,932
I read about it recently
in one of those Harlequin books

1136
01:22:59,007 --> 01:23:01,567
over in the miscellaneous section,
aisle three.

1137
01:23:01,643 --> 01:23:03,338
It sure was different.

1138
01:23:04,346 --> 01:23:05,745
Kind of like a toothbrush...

1139
01:23:06,748 --> 01:23:07,772
but I liked it.

1140
01:23:08,783 --> 01:23:10,774
You can try it if you want to.

1141
01:23:10,852 --> 01:23:11,978
Okay.

1142
01:23:13,621 --> 01:23:14,645
You sure?

1143
01:23:14,723 --> 01:23:17,157
Whatever you're comfortable with.

1144
01:23:26,334 --> 01:23:27,892
I think I'm getting the hang of it.

1145
01:24:09,577 --> 01:24:11,772
<i>There are two types of heroes.</i>

1146
01:24:11,846 --> 01:24:14,007
<i>One changes himself,</i>

1147
01:24:14,082 --> 01:24:16,846
<i>the other changes</i>
<i>those around him.</i>

1148
01:24:16,918 --> 01:24:18,886
Is that some of your
famous lemon meringue?

1149
01:24:18,953 --> 01:24:20,978
Recipe's been in my family
for generations.

1150
01:24:21,056 --> 01:24:22,080
Bring on a slice or two.

1151
01:24:22,157 --> 01:24:23,317
Coming right up. Den?

1152
01:24:23,391 --> 01:24:26,952
<i>Well, I guess in the end,</i>
<i>Ray was both.</i>

1153
01:24:27,028 --> 01:24:28,188
I'll help you, darling.

1154
01:24:28,263 --> 01:24:30,026
Right this way, folks.

1155
01:24:33,535 --> 01:24:35,799
R'ch'lle, you're doing a great job.

1156
01:24:38,940 --> 01:24:40,635
How's the back holding up, hon?

1157
01:24:40,708 --> 01:24:42,198
Just fine, Ray.

1158
01:24:43,745 --> 01:24:47,146
Eddie, I think we're gonna need
to add another pastry chef.

1159
01:24:47,215 --> 01:24:48,682
I'm already on it, Pop.

1160
01:24:50,852 --> 01:24:54,686
Hey, where can a man and his missus
get something to eat around here?

1161
01:24:55,757 --> 01:24:58,089
- How have you been, friend?
- Ray, how you doin'?

1162
01:24:58,159 --> 01:25:00,184
It looks like
we're on the same schedule.

1163
01:25:00,261 --> 01:25:02,092
- Nora, you look really nice.
- Hi.

1164
01:25:02,163 --> 01:25:03,528
- You know Angel?
- Yes. Hi.

1165
01:25:03,598 --> 01:25:05,361
Well, we were just driving around,

1166
01:25:05,433 --> 01:25:07,264
and we thought
maybe we'd come to see

1167
01:25:07,335 --> 01:25:09,462
what kind of progress
you were making.

1168
01:25:09,537 --> 01:25:13,496
I wanna tell you, Ray,
you got it all.

1169
01:25:13,575 --> 01:25:15,167
I am so proud of you.

1170
01:25:15,243 --> 01:25:17,643
Well, couldn't have done it
without you.

1171
01:25:17,712 --> 01:25:19,373
I know that.

1172
01:25:21,015 --> 01:25:23,540
How about a table
for a couple hungry people?

1173
01:25:23,618 --> 01:25:25,279
Oh, by the way,

1174
01:25:25,353 --> 01:25:28,049
I heard that meringue is to die for.

1175
01:25:31,025 --> 01:25:32,049
Right this way.

1176
01:25:33,361 --> 01:25:37,991
<i>Maybe the American dream</i>
does <i>still exist,</i>

1177
01:25:38,066 --> 01:25:40,398
<i>even for my friend Ray...</i>

1178
01:25:40,468 --> 01:25:44,007
<i>and even in a place like Trona.</i>

1179
01:27:44,132 --> 01:27:45,132
Subtitles by LeapinLar
